observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the:

Inventory Committee to submit the complete and accurate RPCPPE not later than January 31 of each year in observance with Section 490 of GAAM, Volume I; 

GSO to maintain an updated property cards for proper upkeep and monitoring of properties; 

Municipal Accountant to prepare necessary adjusting entries to reclassify the CIP-Infrastructure Assets and CIP-Buildings and Other Structures to the appropriate asset accounts and in coordination with the OIC-Municipal Engineer, provide supporting documents to verify the status of the projects recorded in the CIP accounts.  Thereafter, adjust the affected PPE accounts for their fair and accurate presentation in the financial statements; and

GSO and Municipal Accountant to reconcile the property records with the ledger cards of the Accounting Office and that all discrepancies between physical and book inventories must be investigated and cleared immediately.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the: 

BAC to strictly comply with the provisions of the 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184 to establish the regularity of the procurement process and award of contracts; 

Municipal Accountant to check the completeness of supporting documents prescribed under Section 9.1 of COA Circular No. 2012-001 before processing payments to ensure compliance with pertinent sections of the 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184 and to establish the legality, validity and propriety of the disbursements; 

Concerned offices (BAC and Accounting) to submit the required supporting documents prescribed under the 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184 and COA Circular No. 2012-001 for further evaluation as basis for the Audit Team’s subsequent action;

The OIC-Municipal Engineer to (i) compute the ABC in accordance with DPWH DO No. 197 dated October 7, 2016 to avoid misapplication of mark-ups and to prevent overstatement of ABCs; and (ii) ensure that all information required on project billboards are completely filled-up; and

Municipal Treasurer to require written authorization from the contractors, if the claimant of check payments is other than the payee.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the: 

BAC to strictly comply with the provisions of RA No. 9184 and its 2016 Revised IRR to establish the regularity of the award of contract; 

Municipal Accountant to check the completeness of supporting documents prescribed under Section 9.1 of COA Circular No. 2012-001 before processing payments to determine compliance with the given Act and to establish the legality, validity and propriety of the disbursements; 

Concerned offices (BAC and Accounting) to submit the required supporting documents as discussed in the preceding paragraphs in accordance with the same Act and COA Circular No. 2012-001 for further evaluation as basis for the Audit Team’s subsequent action; and 

Municipal Treasurer to require written authorization from the suppliers if the claimant of check payment is other than the payee.

We recommended the Municipal Mayor to require the:

Assigned bonded personnel to issue AF No. 51 to acknowledge receipt of collections from issuance of NBS testing kits and to remit the same to the Municipal Treasurer;

Municipal Accountant to ensure that disbursements are supported with complete documents, processed through the proper procedural flow, certified by the proper signatories and approved by the Municipal Mayor to establish the validity of claims;

BAC to procure NBS testings kits in accordance with RA No. 9184 and its related issuances to establish regularity of the procurement process; and

Municipal Health Officer and Clinical Laboratory staff to check the accuracy of the NBS Kit utilization report and submit the same to the Accounting Department for proper recording in the books of accounts.

