We recommended that the LDRRM Officer:

prepare and submit the LDRRMF Investment Plan to reflect current year appropriation for QRF in lump-sum and the four disaster thematic areas, namely: prevention and mitigation, preparedness, response and rehabilitation and recovery, with details as to projects and activities to be funded, as well as the list of projects and activities to be funded out of the unexpended LDRRM Fund of previous years; 

in case there is a change in the previously proposed projects, see to it that the MDRRM Council is guided by the NDRRMC-DBM-DILG JMC No. 2013-1 dated March 25, 2013 wherein the unexpended balance may be released and utilized for new expenditure items upon submission of a revised AIP as approved by the SB and the LCE upon the recommendation of the MDRRM Council and in accordance with the disaster plan;

consider increasing appropriation intended for acquisition of DRRM equipages in the LDRRMF Plan and prioritize the acquisition of the lacking DRRM equipment, tools and paraphernalia to comply with the minimum standards and pursuant to DILG Memorandum Circular No. 2012-73.  This is to complement the existing equipage already available at the DRRM Office; and

hasten the requisitions of items needed to maintain pre-positioned food packs and hygiene kits for at least 500 families at any given time in compliance with the minimum standards and pursuant to NDRRMC-DBM-DILG JMC No. 2013-1 dated March 25, 2013.

